BRAZIL DAYBOOK: Mantega in Washington, Economic Growth Forecasts

-- B y   H e l d e r   M a r i n h o
-- 
2011-04-15T03:00:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-15/brazil-daybook-mantega-in-washington-economic-growth-forecasts.html
Finance Minister  Guido Mantega 
speaks to reporters in Washington at 4 p.m. New York time, after
meeting with finance ministers and central bankers of the Group
of 20 nations.  WHAT TO WATCH:
*Planning Minister Miriam Belchior speaks to reporters in
Brasilia about budget guidelines for 2012 at 2:30 p.m. *Brazil’s
largest manufacturing association, known as CNI, releases new
estimates for economic growth and inflation at 11 a.m.
*Executives of phone company Oi meet with Communications
Minister Paulo Bernardo in Brasilia.
*President Dilma Rousseff continues her visit to China, heas
bilateral meetings with leaders of Russia,  South Africa  and
India.  ECONOMY:
*FGV broad inflation index IGP-10 at 8 a.m.  EQUITIES:
*Hypermarcas (HYPE3 BZ) sold $750 Million of 10-year notes
*Oi (TNLP3 BZ) Chief Executive Officer Luiz Eduardo Falco will
leave the post
*Itau Unibanco (ITUB4 BZ) agreed to pay 725 million reais for a
49 percent stake in Carrefour’s Banco CSF SA  MARKETS
*The Bovespa index fell 0.3 percent to 66,278.89.
*The real rose 0.5 percent to 1.5782 per dollar.  To contact the reporter on this story:
